#define CSL_INTAGGR_EVT_DETECT_MODE_RISING_EDGE   ((uint32_t) 1U)

Clock synchronous rising edge

#define CSL_INTAGGR_INTR_MODE_FLAG   ((uint32_t) 0x80000000U)

The CSL_INTAGGR_INTR_MODE_FLAG macro can be used to specify that the globalEventOutIdx parameter(s) to the CSL_intaggrMapEventRxCntEvent, CSL_intaggrEnableEventMulticast, and CSL_intaggrMapUnmappedEventToEvent functions contain an interrupt status bit value instead of an event index.

#define CSL_intaggrMapEventToIntr   CSL_intaggrMapEventIntr

These defines map more meaningful function names to prior API function names.
